# CODEOWNERS — minimal money-path hard gate.
#
# Only DB migrations require a code-owner review in GitHub. Migrations are
# irreversible in production, so they keep an independent second approval (from
# a collaborator other than the PR author — GitHub's self-approval rule).
#
# All OTHER money-path changes (x402 / payments / machine-payments /
# payment-coverage / allowance-module / agentAuth / release tooling) are NOT
# hard-gated here. The autonomous PR loop gates them in-session: it pauses such
# a PR and asks whoever is running the loop to approve before it merges. A
# money-path PR created OUTSIDE the loop merges on green CI alone — that is the
# accepted trade-off for low contributor friction at this stage.
#
# See docs/contributing/autonomous-pr-loop.md ("Money-path safety model").

